I'll tell you what.

17:56.520 --> 17:58.079
I'll do the squeezing.

17:59.954 --> 18:01.789
Hey, you.

18:01.790 --> 18:03.207
What did you do with the bag?

18:03.208 --> 18:04.583
Yeah, what'd you do with it?

18:04.584 --> 18:06.336
I didn't find any bag.

18:09.672 --> 18:11.800
I didn't find a bag!

18:12.640 --> 18:13.801
(MAN GRUNTS)

18:13.843 --> 18:15.887
MAN: Make him talk.

18:18.681 --> 18:21.433
MAN: Everybody saw you.

18:21.434 --> 18:24.103
Just tell us!

18:24.104 --> 18:26.438
MAN: Make him talk.

18:26.439 --> 18:27.899
Where is the bag, huh?

18:32.195 --> 18:35.614
AGUSTIN: I don't know!

18:35.615 --> 18:38.784
Just tell us where it is.

18:38.785 --> 18:40.035
No!

18:40.036 --> 18:41.286
Put his head under again.

18:41.287 --> 18:43.080
Tell us, you dumb-ass.

18:43.081 --> 18:45.500
You have to talk!

18:46.520 --> 18:48.352
(AGUSTIN GASPING)

18:48.419 --> 18:49.962
You've been warned.

18:49.963 --> 18:51.964
You have one day.

18:51.965 --> 18:53.049
One day!

19:01.891 --> 19:03.685
No!

19:10.040 --> 19:13.044
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

19:13.069 --> 19:16.905
Antonia!

19:16.906 --> 19:18.449
Hello?

19:22.720 --> 19:24.040
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

19:27.250 --> 19:30.586
Agustin, what...

19:30.587 --> 19:31.880
Come in. Come in.

19:40.013 --> 19:42.806
I don't want to know
what happened.

19:42.807 --> 19:45.018
Hey, he's bleeding!

19:46.561 --> 19:47.811
Yes, darling.

19:47.812 --> 19:51.106
He fell, but we
are helping him.

19:51.107 --> 19:52.900
Stop looking and get ready.

19:52.901 --> 19:54.776
The bus will leave without you.

19:54.777 --> 19:56.528
I see blood all the time, Mom.
Let me watch.

19:56.529 --> 19:58.989
Please, dear. Go and get ready.

19:58.990 --> 20:01.742
Am I staying at the hospital
or with Aunt Mary?

20:01.743 --> 20:03.160
With Aunt Mary.

20:03.161 --> 20:05.412
Go and get your snacks
from the kitchen.

20:05.413 --> 20:06.622
Go on!

20:06.623 --> 20:07.915
Poor kid.

20:07.916 --> 20:09.458
Is he still waiting
for a donor?

20:09.459 --> 20:11.376
The rich are first in line.

20:11.377 --> 20:12.962
We can leave if you want.

20:14.797 --> 20:16.798
That's not necessary.

20:16.799 --> 20:19.636
But let me make something clear.

20:21.304 --> 20:23.640
I don't want to see you here
when I get back.

20:25.433 --> 20:27.018
You're leaving us
alone in your house?

20:28.895 --> 20:30.188
I trust you.

20:32.440 --> 20:33.601
(SIGHS)

20:33.608 --> 20:34.858
Besides,

20:34.859 --> 20:37.528
why would I be afraid of someone
who carries an altar everywhere?

20:42.116 --> 20:44.576
ANTONIA: All right.

20:44.577 --> 20:46.119
Use all the bandages you need.

20:46.120 --> 20:47.372
Let's go, darling.

20:52.377 --> 20:53.585
Did you bring your pajamas?

20:53.586 --> 20:54.795
Yes, Mom.

20:54.796 --> 20:56.255
Okay, sweetheart.

20:56.256 --> 20:57.936
And your games so you can play
with Matias?

21:01.844 --> 21:03.137
Keep your sweater on, okay?

21:14.315 --> 21:16.692
AGUSTIN: God forgive me,

21:16.693 --> 21:20.028
but why can't they fight me
one-on-one?

21:20.029 --> 21:23.699
I'll bash their heads
in with my oar.

21:23.700 --> 21:27.911
I'll grind off their faces
with my engine propeller.

21:27.912 --> 21:29.955
Then they'll see.

21:29.956 --> 21:32.041
What were you doing
in the church?

21:36.629 --> 21:38.715
Please don't tell anyone.

21:42.260 --> 21:44.679
What did you ask from God?

21:46.848 --> 21:49.683
That those damn guys
would leave town

21:49.684 --> 21:51.978
and let me work in peace.

21:58.800 --> 22:01.838
(INTENSE MUSIC)

22:10.880 --> 22:12.041
(WHIRRING)

22:23.880 --> 22:24.927
(SAFETY CLICKS)

22:27.280 --> 22:28.441
(TRIGGER CLICK ECHOES)

22:38.566 --> 22:40.151
MAN: Who the hell is this guy?

22:42.236 --> 22:46.281
Get on your knees
and ask God for forgiveness.

22:46.282 --> 22:48.743
This guy's nuts.

22:52.372 --> 22:53.453
MAN: Go get him. Kill him!

23:02.340 --> 23:03.966
We'll show the son of a bitch.

23:09.040 --> 23:10.269
Wah!

23:12.800 --> 23:14.120
Ahh!

23:23.680 --> 23:24.727
(BOOMING)

23:26.160 --> 23:27.207
(CRACKS)

23:29.283 --> 23:30.534
MAN: Let's kill this guy!

23:30.535 --> 23:31.701
Come on, get up!

23:31.702 --> 23:32.953
Kill him!

23:32.954 --> 23:34.205
We'll massacre him!

23:48.320 --> 23:49.765
(MAN GROANS)

23:56.561 --> 23:58.479
MAN: Come on. Let's get him.

24:12.280 --> 24:13.327
(BLOOD SLOSHING)

24:15.440 --> 24:18.330
(MAN MOANING)

24:36.840 --> 24:39.844
(ENGINE REVVING)

24:41.397 --> 24:43.691
No, please don't!

24:45.360 --> 24:46.714
(BLOOD SLOSHING)

24:51.320 --> 24:52.998
(DRAMATIC MUSICAL FLOURISH)

24:52.999 --> 24:55.828
Ask for forgiveness,
and you will be forgiven.

25:06.120 --> 25:09.124
(SOMBER MUSIC)

25:30.440 --> 25:33.444
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

26:29.920 --> 26:32.924
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

26:42.840 --> 26:44.365
(HANDLE CLICKS)

27:02.480 --> 27:03.800
(KNOCKING)

27:10.212 --> 27:11.756
Come in.

27:16.677 --> 27:18.720
Did I not make myself clear?

27:18.721 --> 27:20.180
I don't want you in my house.

27:20.181 --> 27:22.683
I don't want you here anymore.

27:24.226 --> 27:25.977
It's too dangerous.

27:25.978 --> 27:28.147
I have enough
problems as it is.

27:30.274 --> 27:31.983
Please.

27:31.984 --> 27:35.654
If I walk out that door,
they'll kill me.

27:35.655 --> 27:38.782
I can't leave.

27:38.783 --> 27:40.659
Do it for me.

27:40.660 --> 27:42.911
I can help around the house.

27:42.912 --> 27:44.245
I can clean,

27:44.246 --> 27:45.497
I can cook,

27:45.498 --> 27:48.124
but please let me stay.

27:48.125 --> 27:50.543
No one knows we're here.

27:50.544 --> 27:52.712
Otherwise, they
would've come already.

27:52.713 --> 27:54.507
I'm begging you,
please let me stay.

27:57.510 --> 27:59.094
Where's the broom?

27:59.095 --> 28:00.846
Why are they looking for you?

28:03.849 --> 28:05.934
Well, I...

28:05.935 --> 28:09.104
I know I messed up, but...

28:09.105 --> 28:11.774
I didn't know this was going
to happen, I swear!

28:13.901 --> 28:15.194
What did you do?

28:17.363 --> 28:19.948
I was working,

28:19.949 --> 28:23.202
and a bag full of money
got trapped in my net.

28:25.246 --> 28:26.664
I got scared.

28:28.541 --> 28:31.793
I wanted to give it back,
but there was no one around.

28:31.794 --> 28:34.755
So I took it to the church...

28:36.465 --> 28:38.216
To give to the priest,
to donate it,

28:38.217 --> 28:41.845
but he wasn't there,
so I hid it.

28:41.846 --> 28:45.724
Later, the gringo's men
beat the crap out of me.

28:45.725 --> 28:49.562
I thought no one had seen me,
but I guess they did.

28:51.105 --> 28:54.774
I need a safe place
to leave Agustin.

28:54.775 --> 28:56.484
I'm returning the money.

28:56.485 --> 28:57.986
Are you crazy?

28:57.987 --> 29:01.990
Those men will
kill you on sight!

29:01.991 --> 29:04.784
We need a different plan.

29:04.785 --> 29:07.371
There is no other plan.

29:21.677 --> 29:23.179
I know a safe place.

29:38.800 --> 29:40.484
(DOOR CREAKING)

29:40.529 --> 29:42.071
So...

29:42.072 --> 29:44.283
What I was thinking
we could do...

29:46.577 --> 29:52.373
I was thinking I could dive
underwater, you know?

29:52.374 --> 29:54.584
I can swim for about 100 meters.

29:54.585 --> 29:56.336
I'm really agile underwater.

29:56.337 --> 29:59.798
That's my job,
my specialty, so...

29:59.799 --> 30:01.258
Where can I find them?

30:04.887 --> 30:07.472
About 300 meters
from the church,

30:07.473 --> 30:09.599
there's a wooden house.

30:09.600 --> 30:11.559
That's where they hang out.

30:11.560 --> 30:15.688
For certain,
you'll find them there,

30:15.689 --> 30:19.108
and for certain,
they'll send you to hell.

30:19.109 --> 30:20.486
What do I do if they kill you?

30:29.520 --> 30:30.874
(TAPPING ON WINDOW)

30:36.001 --> 30:37.961
MAN: Boss!

30:37.962 --> 30:39.838
Who is this fuckhead?

30:39.839 --> 30:41.966
He says he knows
where the money is.

30:44.468 --> 30:46.095
PIEDRA: Search him.

30:49.849 --> 30:51.517
Turn around.

30:55.920 --> 30:58.958
(MYSTERIOUS MUSIC)

31:12.955 --> 31:14.539
Where's the money?

31:14.540 --> 31:16.124
In the church,

31:16.125 --> 31:18.042
next to the altar.

31:18.043 --> 31:21.004
And what is it that you want?

31:21.005 --> 31:24.173
For you to take the money
and let it all end there.

31:24.174 --> 31:27.802
No violence and no killing.

31:27.803 --> 31:31.764
That's not how we do things
here, you dumb fuck.

31:31.765 --> 31:34.517
But if the money
is where you say it is,

31:34.518 --> 31:36.436
then maybe we can negotiate.

31:36.437 --> 31:37.812
Crab!

31:37.813 --> 31:39.731
If he moves a single hair,

31:39.732 --> 31:42.650
fill his head with lead.

31:42.651 --> 31:43.902
I'll call you from the church.

31:43.903 --> 31:45.154
Let's go.

31:46.760 --> 31:49.798
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

31:59.209 --> 32:00.752
It's not where he
said it would be.

32:00.753 --> 32:02.254
Search every fucking corner!

32:07.468 --> 32:08.635
Well?

32:08.636 --> 32:09.678
Nothing.

32:16.280 --> 32:19.270
(PHONE RINGING)

32:19.271 --> 32:20.648
Boss?

32:23.859 --> 32:26.153
You bastard! I'll kill you!

32:34.480 --> 32:36.278
(SQUISHING)

32:43.720 --> 32:45.165
(SCREAMING)

33:12.040 --> 33:13.235
(MAN GRUNTS)

33:15.040 --> 33:18.010
(GUNSHOTS)

33:35.360 --> 33:38.398
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

33:48.240 --> 33:51.244
(FLY BUZZING)

33:52.920 --> 33:54.600
BRADOCK: (IN ENGLISH) You dance very good.

34:06.253 --> 34:09.714
Mr. Bradock.

34:09.715 --> 34:12.134
Hello, Piedra.

34:15.344 --> 34:16.929
Hi. How are you?

34:16.929 --> 34:19.181
Have you stopped
scratching your balls?

34:19.183 --> 34:21.391
We have a new problem, sir.

34:21.393 --> 34:24.645
Someone killed
a bunch of our men.

34:24.646 --> 34:27.399
I think it might
be The Redeemer.

34:29.568 --> 34:32.652
What? Are you sure?

34:32.654 --> 34:34.489
He has the tattoo on his back,

34:34.489 --> 34:36.574
and he killed 12 armed men.

34:40.920 --> 34:44.288
El Redentor is here.

34:59.520 --> 35:02.490
El Redentor and El Alacran?

35:09.480 --> 35:12.791
I mean, those are
really cool names.

35:41.520 --> 35:42.635
You guys got anything?

35:45.480 --> 35:47.005
All right.

36:14.560 --> 36:17.564
(FOREBODING MUSIC)

36:28.520 --> 36:30.062
AGUSTIN: (IN SPANISH) A lot of money.

36:30.063 --> 36:31.355
Yes.

36:31.356 --> 36:34.109
It's all here. All of it.

36:40.866 --> 36:42.033
Calm down.

36:42.034 --> 36:43.659
This is the only chance I have

36:43.660 --> 36:45.912
to save my son, Tommy.

36:45.913 --> 36:47.915
That's not my problem.

36:52.836 --> 36:55.254
Give it back to me!

36:55.255 --> 36:57.840
Who do you think you are?
The divine avenger?

36:57.841 --> 37:00.051
Clearly, you have no idea
what it's like to raise a child.

37:00.052 --> 37:02.303
Antonia...

37:02.304 --> 37:04.722
Do you think because you go
around with your little saints

37:04.723 --> 37:06.642
that you get to decide
what is right and wrong?

37:08.060 --> 37:10.896
Don't, Antonia. He's dangerous.

37:15.442 --> 37:18.027
Please.

37:18.028 --> 37:21.031
In your hands is the only
chance I have to save him.

37:42.600 --> 37:43.647
(MOANING)

37:44.920 --> 37:45.967
(SHRIEKING)

38:01.760 --> 38:03.808
(SCREAMING)

38:09.720 --> 38:12.724
(INTENSE MUSIC)

38:34.080 --> 38:37.084
(SOBBING)

38:58.560 --> 38:59.755
(SCREAMS)

39:05.200 --> 39:06.281
(TRIGGER CLICKS)

39:10.360 --> 39:11.407
(TRIGGER CLICKS)

39:18.400 --> 39:21.404
(MYSTERIOUS MUSIC)

39:51.120 --> 39:52.713
(DOOR CREAKS)

40:01.691 --> 40:03.692
Thank you for your decision.

40:03.693 --> 40:06.238
I'm not the one who decides.

40:10.617 --> 40:12.618
Where are you going now?

40:12.619 --> 40:14.621
I need to be alone.

40:17.600 --> 40:20.604
(SOLEMN MUSIC)

40:36.935 --> 40:38.436
See?

40:38.437 --> 40:39.603
See what I mean?

40:39.604 --> 40:41.397
I told you.

40:41.398 --> 40:43.315
The guy's crazy!

40:43.316 --> 40:45.234
Be quiet.

40:45.235 --> 40:48.154
I wonder...

40:48.155 --> 40:51.740
What happened to make
him so crazy?

40:51.741 --> 40:54.369
Let's just leave him alone.

40:55.480 --> 40:56.675
(WHIRRING)

41:01.418 --> 41:02.585
What's he doing?

41:02.586 --> 41:03.795
He's going to kill himself!

41:05.755 --> 41:06.798
Stop!

41:08.925 --> 41:10.468
What are you doing?

41:10.469 --> 41:12.553
Why are you asking God?

41:12.554 --> 41:15.973
Do you believe it's God's will
that my son is going to die?

41:15.974 --> 41:17.183
I asked you for help.

41:17.184 --> 41:20.144
No one else but you.

41:20.145 --> 41:22.688
It's simple, really.

41:22.689 --> 41:24.691
You are the only one
who decides.

41:36.840 --> 41:37.887
(SAFETY CLICKS)

41:42.167 --> 41:43.418
Please.

41:46.720 --> 41:47.915
(GASPS)

41:49.508 --> 41:50.759
Amen.

41:58.440 --> 42:01.444
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

42:37.514 --> 42:40.934
Sir, I found this hidden
in the bedroom.

42:49.960 --> 42:51.360
BRADOCK: (IN ENGLISH) Well, listen.

43:08.480 --> 43:10.471
I think it would-well, I mean,

43:17.880 --> 43:20.645
No, I'm gonna go,
and I'll call you later.

43:23.810 --> 43:24.727
I found this.

43:24.728 --> 43:26.250
Oh.

43:32.160 --> 43:34.117
The Redeemer is in town.

44:19.658 --> 44:20.824
(IN SPANISH) Hello?

44:20.825 --> 44:22.534
Tommy!

44:22.535 --> 44:25.037
How are you?

44:25.038 --> 44:26.497
Yes, darling,
in a little while.

44:26.498 --> 44:28.374
He's leaving again.

44:28.375 --> 44:31.293
Yes, a little.

44:31.294 --> 44:33.587
No, you don't need
to come back here.

44:33.588 --> 44:35.214
I'll pick you up
as soon as I can.

44:35.215 --> 44:36.632
Okay?

44:36.633 --> 44:38.676
I'll take you
anywhere you want.

44:38.677 --> 44:40.052
Deal?

44:40.053 --> 44:41.387
Listen, sweetheart.

44:41.388 --> 44:42.680
I have to go now.

44:42.681 --> 44:44.348
I will call you
in a little bit.

44:44.349 --> 44:45.600
I love you. Bye.

44:47.680 --> 44:50.684
(FOREBODING MUSIC)

44:56.194 --> 44:59.279
What is it that you're thinking
of doing, my friend?

44:59.280 --> 45:01.865
To kill them all, perhaps?

45:01.866 --> 45:03.701
Because these guys,

45:03.702 --> 45:05.327
even if they get
their money back,

45:05.328 --> 45:07.706
will follow us to hell
just to kill us.

45:12.001 --> 45:14.962
That's what you have to do.

45:14.963 --> 45:16.422
Kill them all.

45:16.423 --> 45:18.507
One by one.

45:18.508 --> 45:20.593
Even the gringo.

45:22.637 --> 45:25.807
That's the only way
you can end this thing.

45:30.019 --> 45:31.603
There will be another
drug deal.

45:31.604 --> 45:34.149
That will lead me
to the gringo.

45:39.821 --> 45:42.532
That's exactly what I
was about to say.

45:44.440 --> 45:47.444
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

46:48.800 --> 46:51.804
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

47:19.880 --> 47:22.884
(INTENSE MUSIC)

47:43.240 --> 47:43.740
♪♪

48:01.920 --> 48:04.924
(GUNSHOTS)

48:15.280 --> 48:16.327
(GUNSHOT)

48:23.560 --> 48:24.755
(GRUNTS)

48:53.520 --> 48:56.524
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

49:37.200 --> 49:38.793
(GRUNTS)

49:51.000 --> 49:54.004
(GRUNTING)

50:19.560 --> 50:22.564
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

50:53.440 --> 50:54.635
(LOUD SLAM)

51:06.400 --> 51:09.404
(GRUNTING)

51:27.600 --> 51:29.045
(CRUNCHING)

51:34.600 --> 51:37.604
(MELANCHOLY MUSIC)

52:15.383 --> 52:16.925
Has he been back long?

52:16.926 --> 52:18.760
No, not long.

52:18.761 --> 52:20.095
He didn't say anything,

52:20.096 --> 52:21.972
just walked straight
to his corner.

52:21.973 --> 52:23.932
I don't know what he's
doing in there.

52:23.933 --> 52:26.518
I've never met
someone so strange.

52:26.519 --> 52:29.522
I'd be shocked if he's
said so much as 10 words.

52:31.315 --> 52:34.651
Do you know why he wears
that Virgin del Carmen necklace?

52:34.652 --> 52:35.819
No. What's it for?

52:35.820 --> 52:38.363
To save himself from purgatory.

52:38.364 --> 52:40.073
Because he wants
to go to heaven.

52:40.074 --> 52:42.826
Only those who have
sinned a lot wear them.

52:42.827 --> 52:44.619
What did he do?

52:44.620 --> 52:47.539
I'm grateful for
what he did for me,

52:47.540 --> 52:49.833
but he scares me.

52:49.834 --> 52:53.837
That ritual he does has nothing
to do with true religion.

52:53.838 --> 52:56.214
And which one is
the true religion?

52:56.215 --> 52:58.842
The one from God, of course.

52:58.843 --> 53:00.802
He's just like anyone else.

53:00.803 --> 53:04.264
A mere mortal who's scared
and wants to be saved.

53:04.265 --> 53:06.099
Just like the rest of us.

53:06.100 --> 53:08.768
By pointing a gun to his head?

53:08.769 --> 53:10.187
No, that's not the way.

53:10.188 --> 53:11.897
I don't know
what the right way is,

53:11.898 --> 53:14.149
and I'm not one to say, either.

53:14.150 --> 53:18.820
All I know is if we're not
capable of forgiving ourselves,

53:18.821 --> 53:20.864
then no one else will.

53:20.865 --> 53:23.909
If you aren't capable
of accepting your dark side,

53:23.910 --> 53:26.786
then that darkness will
follow you like a shadow.

53:26.787 --> 53:29.873
The more you deny it,
the stronger it gets.

53:29.874 --> 53:33.752
But if you accept it,
it goes away.

53:33.753 --> 53:35.128
It's strange.

53:35.129 --> 53:39.633
But it's what I have
learned in life.

53:39.634 --> 53:43.053
Do you know
what true salvation is?

53:43.054 --> 53:48.099
Realizing that you're good
and bad at the same time.

53:48.100 --> 53:49.851
What?

53:49.852 --> 53:52.562
Did you think you
were 100% good?

53:52.563 --> 53:54.105
Of course!

53:54.106 --> 53:56.359
Can't you see my halo?

54:05.000 --> 54:08.004
(LIGHTHEARTED PIANO MUSIC)

54:16.045 --> 54:17.672
Want something to eat?

54:23.469 --> 54:24.720
Thank you.

54:36.399 --> 54:38.150
Are you all right?

54:54.480 --> 54:57.518
(MICE SQUEAKING)

55:00.673 --> 55:02.633
ALACRAN: Nicky Pardo.

55:06.012 --> 55:10.015
I don't understand how
the cartel's best hit man

55:10.016 --> 55:13.310
could have made
a mistake like that.

55:13.311 --> 55:14.978
I imagine
it never crossed your mind

55:14.979 --> 55:18.940
to let me live, did it?

55:18.941 --> 55:20.400
Look, Pardo.

55:20.401 --> 55:23.862
The conclusion is people
like you and I

55:23.863 --> 55:26.991
cannot have a family.

55:31.560 --> 55:32.755
(SCREAMS)

55:34.498 --> 55:37.334
You should have seen
your wife's face

55:37.335 --> 55:39.503
when I told her about
your double life.

55:56.440 --> 55:57.726
(MAN LAUGHING)

56:15.247 --> 56:18.208
ALACRAN: You have two options.

56:18.209 --> 56:22.004
You can watch your wife
suffer until she dies...

56:25.883 --> 56:28.803
Or you put an end
to her suffering.

56:32.306 --> 56:34.308
WOMAN: Kill the both of us.

56:38.440 --> 56:41.444
(MOURNFUL MUSIC)

56:45.240 --> 56:45.740
♪♪

57:10.680 --> 57:13.684
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

57:47.590 --> 57:50.133
Oh? Huh? Huh?

57:50.134 --> 57:51.759
Six twos.

57:51.760 --> 57:53.970
Six twos?

57:53.971 --> 57:55.839
No, no, no!

57:55.840 --> 57:57.672
Piedra, what's going on, buddy?

57:57.975 --> 57:59.976
Two more of our men
have been killed,

57:59.977 --> 58:02.145
but I don't think
it was The Redeemer.

58:02.146 --> 58:03.606
I found this.

58:07.480 --> 58:11.519
No, no, no, no!

58:11.572 --> 58:12.864
He is here!

58:12.865 --> 58:14.491
Now we're all fucked!

58:14.492 --> 58:15.825
We have to leave.

58:15.826 --> 58:17.076
Grab your things, and let's go!

58:17.077 --> 58:18.328
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

58:18.329 --> 58:21.199
Sit down, my friends. Sit down.

58:21.200 --> 58:22.998
Why don't you tell me
what's going on, man?

58:42.686 --> 58:44.103
He's asking if you guys

58:44.104 --> 58:45.439
have thought about
the name thing.

58:49.400 --> 58:51.084
Senior Bradock-Steve-

59:21.350 --> 59:22.309
Asshole.

59:30.276 --> 59:31.526
Sorry, Mr. Steve.

59:31.527 --> 59:32.999
I had to do that.

59:33.000 --> 59:34.411
It's all right. Don't be sorry.

59:47.543 --> 59:49.919
(IN SPANISH) Brothers!

59:49.920 --> 59:51.991
I have a dream.

01:00:11.800 --> 01:00:14.713
So I say that we stay
and we fight.

01:00:29.120 --> 01:00:30.315
Wait. I've got it.

01:00:32.046 --> 01:00:35.757
You go to warehouse.

01:00:35.758 --> 01:00:37.551
Yes, sir.

01:00:49.320 --> 01:00:50.879
We're gonna post up here.

01:00:53.640 --> 01:00:55.688
Cowboy up, boys.

01:01:05.788 --> 01:01:08.300
ANTONIA: Hey!

01:01:08.332 --> 01:01:10.084
You forgot something.

01:01:14.588 --> 01:01:15.839
Thanks.

01:01:20.761 --> 01:01:23.222
Maybe you don't need it anymore?

01:01:37.695 --> 01:01:39.780
Your son is going to be fine.

01:01:43.080 --> 01:01:45.811
(ENGINE TURNS OVER)

01:01:50.400 --> 01:01:53.404
(FOREBODING MUSIC)

01:02:06.720 --> 01:02:09.724
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

01:02:27.828 --> 01:02:29.538
I'll get the boat.

01:02:31.665 --> 01:02:35.209
We'll meet here in two hours.

01:02:35.210 --> 01:02:37.670
Stay here with the money.

01:02:37.671 --> 01:02:39.630
Two hours.

01:02:39.631 --> 01:02:41.340
You go, but I'll wait for him.

01:02:41.341 --> 01:02:43.426
Then all three of us will meet.

01:02:43.427 --> 01:02:45.511
What's wrong with you?

01:02:45.512 --> 01:02:47.430
Don't you realize

01:02:47.431 --> 01:02:49.182
he's going to get
himself killed?

01:02:49.183 --> 01:02:52.394
As long as he's alive,
I'll wait for him.

01:02:54.938 --> 01:02:56.314
Okay.

01:02:56.315 --> 01:02:57.566
Two hours.

01:03:06.450 --> 01:03:07.993
Two hours.

01:03:28.560 --> 01:03:31.564
(INTENSE MUSIC)

01:03:38.315 --> 01:03:39.358
Look out!

01:03:59.040 --> 01:04:02.044
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

01:04:06.593 --> 01:04:09.471
Come on, let's kill
this motherfucker!

01:04:15.880 --> 01:04:18.884
(GRUNTING)

01:04:24.880 --> 01:04:25.927
(MAN SCREAMS)

01:04:43.880 --> 01:04:46.076
(RAPID GUNSHOTS)

01:04:55.934 --> 01:04:57.603
No, no, no, no!

01:05:07.160 --> 01:05:08.446
(SLAMS, DOOR CRACKS)

01:05:20.120 --> 01:05:23.124
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

01:05:43.040 --> 01:05:44.633
(SCREAMING)

01:06:05.280 --> 01:06:06.998
(PANTING)

01:06:45.720 --> 01:06:48.724
(ENGINE RUMBLING)

01:06:57.160 --> 01:07:00.403
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

01:07:10.200 --> 01:07:13.204
(ENGINE SPUTTERS THEN STOPS)

01:07:18.400 --> 01:07:21.916
(ENGINE SPUTTERING)

01:07:53.280 --> 01:07:56.284
(GUNSHOTS)

01:08:00.760 --> 01:08:02.444
(GRUNTING)

01:08:46.200 --> 01:08:47.554
(BOOMING)

01:08:52.200 --> 01:08:52.700
♪♪

01:09:31.840 --> 01:09:34.844
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

01:10:17.800 --> 01:10:18.300
<i>♪♪</i>

01:10:34.720 --> 01:10:37.724
(GRUNTING)

01:10:46.120 --> 01:10:47.599
(BLOOD SLOSHING)

01:10:52.160 --> 01:10:54.834
(PANTING)

01:10:54.876 --> 01:10:57.795
Bradock.

01:10:57.796 --> 01:10:59.672
Blue Bay.

01:10:59.673 --> 01:11:01.841
Last house.

01:11:42.400 --> 01:11:45.404
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

01:12:00.000 --> 01:12:03.004
(TENSE MUSIC)

01:12:44.880 --> 01:12:46.075
(LAUGHING)

01:12:51.240 --> 01:12:52.743
(LOUD SMACK)

01:12:52.744 --> 01:12:54.287
Dumb bastard.

01:12:56.873 --> 01:12:59.375
I love you, son.

01:12:59.376 --> 01:13:00.626
Me, too, Dad.

01:13:00.627 --> 01:13:01.877
Want to play again?

01:13:01.878 --> 01:13:03.128
Okay.

01:13:03.129 --> 01:13:04.296
I'll count.

01:13:04.297 --> 01:13:05.382
You count.

01:13:10.845 --> 01:13:13.097
One, two...

01:13:13.098 --> 01:13:15.099
Three, four...

01:13:15.100 --> 01:13:17.101
Five, six...

01:13:17.102 --> 01:13:19.103
Seven, eight...

01:13:19.104 --> 01:13:20.146
Nine...

01:13:25.819 --> 01:13:27.195
Here I come!

01:13:36.920 --> 01:13:39.924
(GRUNTING)

01:13:49.840 --> 01:13:51.319
(GUNSHOT)

01:13:59.160 --> 01:14:02.164
(SCREAMS)

01:14:31.843 --> 01:14:33.886
I want you to get on your knees

01:14:33.887 --> 01:14:35.972
and ask for forgiveness
for what you have done.

01:14:39.767 --> 01:14:42.395
On your knees, asshole!

01:14:49.068 --> 01:14:52.071
You killed the only thing
I loved in life,

01:14:52.614 --> 01:14:55.825
you piece of shit.

01:14:56.840 --> 01:14:58.035
(GRUNTS)

01:15:00.246 --> 01:15:02.081
On your knees!

01:15:05.320 --> 01:15:06.515
(GRUNTS)

01:15:11.883 --> 01:15:14.009
When I heard you were alive,

01:15:14.010 --> 01:15:17.346
I realized you
were worse than me.

01:15:17.347 --> 01:15:21.225
But neither God
nor the Virgin of Guadalupe

01:15:21.226 --> 01:15:23.602
are going to save you.

01:15:23.603 --> 01:15:27.899
All you have done
won't get you to heaven.

01:15:30.068 --> 01:15:33.028
Did you know that I found
everyone you helped?

01:15:33.029 --> 01:15:36.490
Of course you didn't.

01:15:36.491 --> 01:15:39.201
One by one,

01:15:39.202 --> 01:15:41.453
I made them suffer
until they died,

01:15:41.454 --> 01:15:44.749
just so I can spit it
back in your face!

01:15:47.377 --> 01:15:51.171
And now...

01:15:51.172 --> 01:15:53.550
I only have two left to go.

01:15:56.135 --> 01:15:57.845
Ah!

01:16:03.810 --> 01:16:06.604
Did you enjoy playing
with the gun I left you?

01:16:10.817 --> 01:16:14.987
Now we will all play together.

01:16:14.988 --> 01:16:17.239
Get up!

01:16:17.240 --> 01:16:18.491
Take the gun.

01:16:23.955 --> 01:16:25.831
Take it!

01:16:25.832 --> 01:16:27.750
Don't move.

01:16:34.215 --> 01:16:35.508
Come on, bastard!

01:16:39.012 --> 01:16:40.597
No.

01:16:44.100 --> 01:16:45.267
Come on!

01:16:45.268 --> 01:16:46.519
I can't.

01:16:49.480 --> 01:16:51.312
(CRYING)

01:16:51.316 --> 01:16:54.569
Play or I will kill
her, asshole.

01:16:56.154 --> 01:16:57.864
Do it!

01:16:59.840 --> 01:17:01.001
(GUNSHOT)

01:17:04.203 --> 01:17:05.746
You grab the gun.

01:17:05.747 --> 01:17:07.123
Come on!

01:17:10.835 --> 01:17:12.003
It's your turn now!

01:17:15.120 --> 01:17:18.124
(GASPING)

01:17:21.095 --> 01:17:23.139
Play or he dies!

01:17:45.828 --> 01:17:48.665
Kill the both of us.

01:17:49.520 --> 01:17:51.541
(ALACRAN LAUGHING)

01:17:51.542 --> 01:17:54.545
Do it.

01:17:58.680 --> 01:18:00.671
(SCREAMING)

01:18:12.105 --> 01:18:14.064
He's not going to kill me

01:18:14.065 --> 01:18:16.109
without watching me
suffer first.

01:18:22.040 --> 01:18:23.451
(GUNSHOT)

01:18:26.400 --> 01:18:29.404
(GRUNTING)

01:18:32.920 --> 01:18:35.924
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

01:18:57.400 --> 01:18:59.960
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

01:19:05.960 --> 01:19:08.964
(GRUNTING)

01:19:27.600 --> 01:19:30.604
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

01:20:14.240 --> 01:20:17.244
(GRUNTING)

01:20:26.040 --> 01:20:29.249
(GASPING)

01:20:45.520 --> 01:20:46.020
♪♪

01:21:12.040 --> 01:21:14.714
(CRIES OUT)

01:21:41.280 --> 01:21:42.475
(SCREAMS)

01:22:00.760 --> 01:22:03.764
(INTENSE MUSIC)

01:22:24.040 --> 01:22:25.838
